Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.16,0:05:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But someone from Shioshishio might be faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.76,0:05:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So are you two gonna root for Sakishima-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.80,0:05:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? O-Oh, I'm not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.31,0:05:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, there's Kaname and...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.39,0:05:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii-kun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:05:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.53,0:05:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, I guess it makes sense that \Nyou'd cheer on your Shishio friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.46,0:05:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm gonna root for 'em too!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.24,0:05:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.50,0:05:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Kihara-kun all the way for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.87,0:05:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone in position?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.65,0:05:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.41,0:05:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's weird. Sakishima-kun's \Nslower than I thought he'd be.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.10,0:05:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's probably because he's not used to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.98,0:05:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,To {\i1}swimming{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.35,0:06:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's sort of weird swimming right on the surface of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.26,0:06:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, he's not used to doing the front crawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.86,0:06:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.36,0:06:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Damn it! This is harder than I thought{ it'd be}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.31,0:06:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If I don't love anyone, I won't be so sad!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.03,0:06:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1200)}I don't wanna believe it's hopeless or useless to love someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.93,0:06:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.07,0:06:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.59,0:06:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you okay, Sakishima?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.30,0:06:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.90,0:06:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii-kun got hurt—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.96,0:06:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up, Manaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, both of you come on \Nand get out of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii-kun, let's get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.51,0:06:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you injured your toe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's on duty today?{Is there another name for this? Class monitor? Iunno. We never had some kid who was in charge of errands per day or week or anything, afaik.}{why are you asking me? its not like i had this kind of stuff either}{oh, your response made me laugh}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:06:58.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.04,0:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that works out nicely.{nice coincidence since theyre friends}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.96,0:07:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him to the nurse's office, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.65,0:07:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.35,0:07:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Can Chi— I mean, \Ncan Hiradaira-san come, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.08,0:07:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{replace}Sensei{Teach}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.47,0:07:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go next.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.91,0:07:20.50,Oshit Oshit; Fishy Business,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6\fscx178\fscy178\b1\c&HA12512&\pos(681,564)}'
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.91,0:07:20.50,Oshit Oshit; Fishy Business,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.6\fscx178\fscy178\pos(712,589)\b1\c&HA12512&}Nurse{\alpha&HFF&}'{\alpha&H00&}s Office
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.85,0:07:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do? \NThe nurse isn't here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.60,0:07:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you asking {\i1}me{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.21,0:07:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.10,0:07:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the disinfectant?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.44,0:07:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it. I don't need any.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But our teacher said{ to}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.65,0:07:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.42,0:07:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.20,0:07:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.28,0:07:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.37,0:07:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not very good at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.55,0:07:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii-kun, are you mad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.05,0:08:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.45,0:08:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh, I reek of chlorine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.82,0:08:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.86,0:08:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.36,0:08:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He's way too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.97,0:08:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just because we \Nhardly ever do the front crawl!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.84,0:08:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.81,0:08:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had been in the ocean, \Nyou definitely would've been faster, Hii-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.79,0:08:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, that stings...{he means the attempt to cheer him up}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.66,0:08:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Having to be cheered up by you of all people really stings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.07,0:08:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But everyone else knows you're {can be }really amazing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.28,0:08:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii-chan knows it too!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.31,0:08:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the hell are you bringing up Chisaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.51,0:08:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just go back to class.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.35,0:08:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do this myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.21,0:09:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So lame...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.39,0:09:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{Oh.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.99,0:09:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.39,0:09:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.14,0:09:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That sure took a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.41,0:09:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you two up to \Nin the nurse's office?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.60,0:09:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,"Stop, you perv!"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.50,0:09:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.31,0:09:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing happened! Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.52,0:09:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks guilty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.86,0:09:39.97,Alternative,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.86,0:09:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, really guilty!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.97,0:09:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are such perverts!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.70,0:09:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mukaido-san, go ahead and change.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.63,0:09:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We can take care \Nof cleaning up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.64,0:09:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take that.{lol Kaname's popular with the ladies.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.54,0:10:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't really seem like \Nyou're from the ocean village, Isaki-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.76,0:10:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't think I seem like \NI'm from the surface either, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.13,0:10:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I didn't mean it like that.{saying hes like a surface person would possibly insult him, so shes saying thats not what she meant}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.46,0:10:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sakishima-kun can be a little scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.21,0:10:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's really not. \NDon't you two agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.63,0:10:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd he{funnier this way} know we were here?!{lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.79,0:10:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You kids are from \NHama Elementary, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.78,0:10:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We're {\i1}not{\i0} kids!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.10,0:10:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you done with school for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.97,0:10:33.21,Default,,0,0,0,,W-We were thinking we could maybe help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.21,0:10:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we are!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:35.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Help with what, though?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.61,0:10:38.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, with the Wooden—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.02,0:10:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys are still making \Nthe Wooden Maiden, Isaki-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.21,0:10:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Do you wanna help{ out}{,} too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.95,0:10:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I do!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.92,0:10:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.57,0:10:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you two can help out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.31,0:10:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You're lucky to have such awesome help!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.29,0:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.96,0:11:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumugu-kun, are you going home?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I need to help Gramps today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.27,0:11:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.67,0:11:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is your injury any better?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.17,0:11:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.32,0:11:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought in the cans of veneer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.79,0:11:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I coulda done it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.48,0:11:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Not with your foot in that condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.32,0:11:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,See ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.82,0:11:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.26,0:11:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.98,0:11:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.97,0:11:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.36,0:11:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Sakishima-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.58,0:11:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What the heck, Sakishima?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.19,0:11:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure took your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.66,0:11:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there's nothing left for you to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.56,0:11:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing left!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.91,0:11:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You're{\i0} the one who destroyed it, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.43,0:11:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Boo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.11,0:11:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone {said they }wanted to come and \Nhelp rebuild the broken Wooden Maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.63,0:11:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Except those two. You guys are just here 'cause of Hiradaira-san, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.30,0:11:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What the hell are you saying, you idiot?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.16,0:12:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,W-W-We'll never finish at this rate!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.73,0:12:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, all of you are now my minions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.20,0:12:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Like hell I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.74,0:12:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a pro at the Boatdrift Ceremony!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.02,0:12:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean, "pro"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.28,0:12:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we{'ve} also gotta make offerings—\Nnot just the Wooden Maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.79,0:12:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Offerings?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.28,0:12:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a dresser, a stand, and a table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.71,0:12:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And we need the car, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.26,0:12:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And a TV and video games.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.38,0:12:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wooden Maiden's a gamer now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.85,0:12:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.72,0:12:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Wooden Maiden nowadays is totally hip!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.30,0:12:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, totally hip!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.37,0:12:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They're fitting right in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.96,0:12:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, a little too much, if you ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.02,0:12:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.90,0:12:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii-kun! You shouldn't be walking around on your own yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.85,0:12:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Chii-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.39,0:12:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I just remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.13,0:12:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.04,0:12:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom asked me to \Nstop by the post office.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.06,0:12:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What time does it close, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.63,0:12:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Four o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.95,0:12:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Miuna-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.38,0:12:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm off. See you guys later!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.77,0:13:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii-chan, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.27,0:13:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Um, I—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.78,0:13:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I ask you to forget about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.57,0:13:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.89,0:13:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, Chii-chan, I—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.80,0:13:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you promise?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.04,0:13:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you always do things like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.96,0:13:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But if things stay the way they are, \NI thought it might not be good for you.{bad for her life? happiness? relationships? look at her, shes certainly not happy and distancing herself from the others}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you to decide \Nwhat's good or bad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.13,0:13:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I'm gonna go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.25,0:13:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hii-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.43,0:14:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.41,0:14:07.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I hate this!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.71,0:14:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, too bad for you, boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.24,0:14:13.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiradaira-san already went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.28,0:14:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, shut the hell up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an9}We came 'cause we really \Nwanted to help out!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.87,0:14:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like Manaka's not coming back either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.84,0:14:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}Yeah{,}{Arguably, this is a single interjection, whereas "Yeah, (that's) right" would probably be with the comma.} right!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.69,0:14:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So it really is Manaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.67,0:14:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,She's our center.{horrible pun on her name}{Manakeystone! There's probably no way of putting this into the English subs, lol.}{yeah i can't think of any}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.61,0:14:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mukaido?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.23,0:14:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not with Hiradaira?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.85,0:14:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.18,0:14:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 'cause...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.57,0:14:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,'Cause Chii-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.98,0:14:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,said she didn't want to talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.18,0:14:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And before, Hii-kun... he...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.23,0:14:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumugu, take her to the wharf.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.84,0:15:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going{, Gramps}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.36,0:15:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna go check the cages on the east side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.11,0:15:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.89,0:15:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you get on?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.01,0:15:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Gramps...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,was saying that today seemed \Nlike the perfect day for Tomoebi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.33,0:15:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's "Tomoebi"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.93,0:15:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well, when the weather's really nice and there's a lot of saltflake snow,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.48,0:15:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and then a cold current passes through,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.22,0:15:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks like there are three suns \Nbecause of the refraction or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.33,0:15:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've never seen it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.83,0:15:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii-chan and the guys saw it once, \Nwhen we were all in elementary school.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.99,0:15:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They came to get me,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.46,0:16:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but since I couldn't understand what Chii-chan was saying, I just zoned out.{chii was probably talking about having to watch it together or something and manaka was like "ehhh"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.10,0:16:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid Manaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.31,0:16:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.43,0:16:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm{\i0} the stupid one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.13,0:16:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.37,0:16:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really done with you this time, Manaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.48,0:16:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point unless \Nwe all see it together!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make such a big deal out of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.10,0:16:31.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Doesn't it matter to you too, Hikari?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.13,0:16:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Stupid, stupid Manaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.41,0:16:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii-chan got really mad,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.26,0:16:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which surprised me, so I started crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.42,0:16:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She didn't talk to me for a while after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.13,0:16:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really such a big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.16,0:16:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,She said that if we didn't all see it together,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.06,0:16:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it would have no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.31,0:16:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I kind of get that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.23,0:16:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.85,0:17:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand the desire to share something \Nyou enjoy with the people you really care about.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.73,0:17:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.19,0:17:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe Chii-chan doesn't care about me at all now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why wouldn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.90,0:17:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Because...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.23,0:17:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.41,0:17:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.89,0:17:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you ever finish your sentences?{you said it, bro}{+9999}{japan}{though, i'd like to ask a lot of cr translators the same question}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.14,0:17:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Finish my sentences?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.52,0:17:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, instead of trailing off
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.94,0:17:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,or ending {all your }sentences with "or something"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.37,0:17:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or always being so vague,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.53,0:17:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you should {always }talk without hesitating,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,just like you did when you \Njumped in to help Hikari today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.42,0:17:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.89,0:17:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That just came naturally.{it was the first thing that occured to me}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.75,0:17:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.33,0:17:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So {\i1}that's{\i0} the real you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.02,0:17:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.29,0:17:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You were really cool right then, Mukaido.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.81,0:18:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumugu-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.41,0:18:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sowwy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.87,0:19:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii-chan, Chii-chan, Chii-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.96,0:19:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,H-Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.21,0:19:23.10,Alternative,,0,600,0,,Manaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.07,0:19:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomoebi...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.73,0:19:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were little, you came \Nand got me for this, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.84,0:19:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.90,0:20:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I took too long and was the only one who didn't make it in time{ to see it},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.48,0:20:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you got really mad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.29,0:20:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So mad that I got really \Nsurprised and started crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.55,0:20:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{All }That doesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.51,0:20:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'm going to finish my thought.{about fucking time}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.11,0:20:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry that I wasn't \Nable to see this with you that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.45,0:20:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this why you brought me here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.73,0:20:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I promised!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.83,0:20:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I said we'd see it together \Nnext time, no matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.00,0:20:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope the Wooden Maiden \Nnever gets completed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.58,0:20:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that way, it'd always be summer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.58,0:20:47.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of us would always be building the Wooden Maiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.25,0:20:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd always be together,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.87,0:20:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,playing{ together},
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.31,0:20:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,going to school,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.30,0:20:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.31,0:21:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I always thought \Nthat things didn't need to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.98,0:21:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want them to change.{dont want her environment to change}{I know this is the wrong tense, but it's sooo weird to have this be part of the same thought as the line before and have it not be in the same tense.}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.25,0:21:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't want things to change?{about environment}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.73,0:21:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I think it's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.28,0:21:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.79,0:21:13.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, in spite of all that,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.19,0:21:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want things to change.{about environment}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.51,0:21:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I want us all to stay together forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.87,0:21:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so pretty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish Hikari and Kaname were here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.21,0:21:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.67,0:21:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us seeing the same things,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.60,0:21:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,laughing the same way,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.54,0:21:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and staying friends like this forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.53,0:21:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Manaka for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.36,0:21:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we even realize it, \Nshe's always jumping ahead{taking the first step},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.63,0:21:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,long before any of us.{makes more progress? takes a step? something like that}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.73,0:21:50.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though she's a scaredy-cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.75,0:21:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Even though she's Manaka.
